@NODE "StartMenu" "StartMenu"
@NEXT "Main"
@PREV "Main"
@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}About StartMenu
@{JLEFT}@{APEN 1}
@{BODY}@{B}StartMenu @{UB}is a clone of the @{I}TaskBar@{UI} program by MicroSoft for @{B}Windows95®@{UB}. It
lets you launch programs and scripts easily and painlessly. And it's much,
much more...
@{PAR}
@{PAR}To get the latest version of @{B}StartMenu@{UB}, check out the MoppSoft home page:
@{B}http://www.del.net/users/mopp@{UB}.
@{PAR}
@{PAR}StartMenu is Copyright © 1996 by John Corigliano (jcorig@strauss.udel.edu)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Introduciton" "Introduction"
@NEXT "AboutIcons"
@PREV "Main"
@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}Introduction
@{JLEFT}@{APEN 1}
@{BODY}@{"StartMenu" LINK "StartMenu" 0} is a nice program and it really has some nice features, but lets
face it, the icons that come with it are not really attractive, IMHO.  If you
are like me, you love the @{"MagicWB" LINK "MagicWB" 0} icon designs, and strive to have every icon
conform to the MagicWB look.
@{PAR}
@{PAR}With this small collection of brushes and icons you can have StartMenu's
appearence fit the MagicWB standard.  I know the author of StartMenu stated
that a "feature" of StartMenu was that it "Does not require Magic Workbench".
Well, I like MagicWB icons and its colour scheme so I just had to get
StartMenu to look good on my Workbench, and this is the result.
@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{"Click" LINK "My WB Pic/main"} to see my worbench with Startmenu in MWB style.
@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{PAR}
@{PAR}
BTW, I'd like to thank @{B}Alaxandre Gabriel@{UB} for the ONLY email I received on my first release.  I'm glad
there is at least one person in the world that likes what I have put together and took the time to let
me know about it.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "AboutIcons" "About the Icons and Brushes"
@NEXT "Installation"
@PREV "Introduciton"
@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}About the Icons and Brushes
@{JLEFT}@{APEN 1}
@{BODY}Many of the icons and brushes I just cut and paste from other sources, and I
just did a bit of touch up.  I hope the original artists (who ever they are)
do not mind me doing this to their work.
@{PAR}
@{PAR}The Mini Icons and brushes are all a size of 20x20.  This was done so that
with a text size of 11 points (I use XHelvetica/11) and a StartMenu icon
multiplier of 1.80, the icons and brushes would not be resized and therefore
look distorted.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"
@NEXT "Torchia"
@PREV "AboutIcons"
@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}Installation
@{JLEFT}@{APEN 1}
@{BODY}It is strongly recommended to use the provided installer program to install MagicStartMenu.
NOTE: The installation will overwrite existing icons and images that are currently installed in the StartMenu directory.  However, it will not touch any preferences that you may have set for StartMenu.
@{PAR}@{PAR}
@{APEN 2}Settings for StartSetup
@{APEN 1}@{PAR}@{PAR}
Once that is done you will have to set a few parameters in the StartMenu Setup
program:
@{PAR}@{CODE}
 Under Custom, set the following:

 Misc: Icon Multiplier = 1.80
       Font            = XHelvetica/11
       Spacing         = 0

       Commodities  = ON
       Screens      = ON
       System Prefs = ON
       Logo         = ON
       My Computer  = ON

 Colors: TaskBar             = 130, 130, 130
         StartButton Text    = 255, 255, 255
         StartButton BG      =  56, 112, 168
         Menu Title          =   0,   0,   0
         Menu Title Select   = 255, 255, 255
         Menu BG             = 168, 168, 168
         Menu BG Select      =  56, 112, 168
         Clock               =   0,   0,   0
         Clock BG            = 168, 168, 168
         TaskBar Button Text =   0,   0 ,  0
         TaskBar Button BG   = 168, 168, 168

 (Click @{"HERE" LINK "CustomMisc.iff/main" 0} for an IFF picture of the Custom Settings)

@{BODY}Under @{"Programs" LINK "ProgramsEdit.iff/main" 0}, you may create new submenus under the main program menu item.  If so, you may want to
use an alternate icon image for the drawer the way I do (see @{"my WB pic" LINK "MY WB PIC/main" 0}).  The icon name is
"menu2.bru" or "menu3.bru" and can be found in the main StartMenu directory.
@{PAR}@{PAR}
@{APEN 2}Settings for WCPrefs
@{APEN 1}@{PAR}
@{PAR}@{BODY}For the WinControl Prefs, you may want to have disk windows show up
differently on the TaskBar.  Here is an example template of what I use:
@{PAR}
@{CODE}
 NAME      PATTERN           ICON                       TEXT  BG  OFFSET
 <Volume>  <Volume>#?full#?  StartMenu:Brushes/MiniDisk  -1   10    1

 (Click @{"HERE" LINK "WinCtrlPrefs.iff/main" 0} for an IFF picture of the WinControl Prefs Settings)
@ENDNODE

